snippet.textDisplay: My husband and I make a 24-hour fermented dough, divide it into 2 balls, stretch them on parchment (no flour, but cornmeal is great!), cut the parchment as close to the crusts as possible, and bake them for 6-7 min at 550F on a drying rack tucked in a baking sheet (so there's convection under and over the 'za). Then, we take the crusts out, slide them off the parchment, keep them on the cooling rack + sheet pan contraption, top them with sauce, cheese, and our fav toppings, then send them back into the 550F for about 8 more minutes. It's complicated, but honestly is the best we've come to homemade "pizza oven" pizza.
snippet.textOriginal: My husband and I make a 24-hour fermented dough, divide it into 2 balls, stretch them on parchment (no flour, but cornmeal is great!), cut the parchment as close to the crusts as possible, and bake them for 6-7 min at 550F on a drying rack tucked in a baking sheet (so there's convection under and over the 'za). Then, we take the crusts out, slide them off the parchment, keep them on the cooling rack + sheet pan contraption, top them with sauce, cheese, and our fav toppings, then send them back into the 550F for about 8 more minutes. It's complicated, but honestly is the best we've come to homemade "pizza oven" pizza.
